</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1341,1835]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
Comment: Although the 
<typeStatus box="[476,535,1665,1691]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">types</typeStatus>
of this species have not been found, the characteristics mentioned by Lepeletier, such as the green coloration of the metasoma and the pattern of pilosity of the body make it possible to recognize this species. This species was correctly interpreted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Snelling, R. R." box="[761,936,1737,1763]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 69" refId="ref11488" refString="Snelling, R. R. (1984) Studies on the taxonomy and distribution of American Centridine bees (Hymenoptera: Anthophoridae). Contributions in Science, Los Angeles County Museum of Natural History, 347, 1 - 69." type="journal article" year="1984">Snelling (1984)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[991,1214,1737,1763]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref10644" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Orgs.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[1073,1123,1737,1763]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
. According to these latter authors, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[317,419,1773,1799]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis box="[317,336,1773,1799]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[352,419,1774,1799]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs exclusively in South America with distribution records in 
<collectingCountry box="[1177,1248,1773,1799]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1261,1432,1773,1799]" name="French Guiana" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,238,1809,1835]" name="Guyana" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Guyana</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[293,399,1809,1835]" name="Paraguay" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
